article.description: Lo scores 15, leads Columbia over Colgate 69-64
article.headline: Lo scores 15, leads Columbia over Colgate 69-64
article.linkText: Lo scores 15, leads Columbia over Colgate 69-64
article.story: NEW YORK -- Maodo Lo scored 15 points and Isaac Cohen dished out a career-high 10 assists to lead Columbia to a 69-64 victory over Colgate on Sunday. Colgate led 36-31 with 18:49 remaining. Columbia answered with Jeff Coby's bucket, and Kyle Castlin added eight straight points to give the Lions a 41-39 lead with 15:25 left, and they led the rest of the way. Cory Osetkowski scored 14 points, Steve Frankoski had 13 points and Castlin finished with 12 for Columbia (7-4). Cohen also had three blocks and grabbed eight boards for the Lions, who outrebounded the Raiders 33-16. Ethan Jacobs scored 26 points on 9-of-18 shooting to lead Colgate (3-10). Matt McMullen added 12 points, and Austin Tillotson and Luke Roh had 10 points apiece for the Raiders, who have lost three-straight.
